This paper proposes a theoretical framework for stochastic optimization algorithms, which is likely to fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it deals with optimization algorithms for training models. The paper also mentions the use of Bayesian inference, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of stochastic control with asymmetric information suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also deals with differential equations, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and neural networks (cs.NE).
